CS 6314.002 - Practice Work 6

Due date: October 22, 2018, 11:59pm

On an html page, provide a form for the user to enter an address. When the user clicks on the “Search” button:

Using Google Maps API, first find the latitude and longitude for the given address.

Find all nearby pharmacies for that latitude and longitude (within 1500 meters).

Show/mark them on Google maps.


Resources:

https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/tutorial
https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/geocoding/start
https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/places


https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/examples/geocoding-simple






